THE Verulam Regional Court has sentenced Mduduzi Kwazi Nkomo (29) to 20 years in jail for killing his girlfriend. Nkomo arrived at the home of Ntshengisile Dladla (32) and knocked on the door. When she refused to open, he kicked it open and entered. ALSO READ:Â CAR CRASHES INTO TREE! He then stabbed Ntshengisile multiple times with a knife and drill. The victim was declared dead at the scene by paramedics. Police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbele said the accused also attempted to kill himself, but survived. A case of murder was opened at Tongaat cop shop and the accused was immediately arrested. He was kept in jail until his sentencing.